translated: Ernerot, Josef Erik, provincial doctor, Gothenburg, now Kolsback, born on 16/11/06 in Uppsala. Married in 1938 to Dolly Margareta Engberg. Children: Hans Erik, born in 1939 and Karl Thorbjörn, born in 1943. Education: completed secondary school in 1925; bachelor's degree in medicine in 1929; medical license in 1935, all obtained in Uppsala. Work experience: assistant doctor at the surgical department of Sundsvall hospital in 1935-36; the same position in Söderköping hospital in 1936; interim first and second assistant doctor at Gallivare hospital in 1937; interim third assistant doctor at Uddevalla hospital's surgical department in 1937-38; second assistant doctor at Gothenburg's hospital for disabled in 1938; third assistant doctor at Uddevalla hospital's surgical department in 1939; first and second assistant doctor there in 1940-42; assistant doctor at Sahlgr. women's clinic in Gothenburg in 1942-46; the same position at Gustaf V Jubilee clinic in Gothenburg in 1946-47; former provincial doctor in Kolsback since 1947. Published a few minor works in obstetrics and gynecology in 1943-46.
